Generate Anki-style flashcards for the following list of concepts.

Domain: {{.Domain}}
Language: {{.Language}}
Concepts:
{{- range .Concepts}}
- {{.}}
{{- end}}

Rules:
- Generate 2–3 flashcards per concept covering different angles: definition, example recognition, common mistake avoidance
- Each card tests exactly one thing — no compound questions
- front_text is a clear question or cloze prompt; back_text is the concise direct answer
- Cards must be self-contained (no reference to "the list above" or "as mentioned")
- Include the concept name in the "tags" array

Respond with a JSON object in exactly this format (no extra keys):
{
  "flashcards": [
    {
      "front_text": "What is X?",
      "back_text": "...",
      "bloom_level": "remember",
      "tags": ["{{.Domain}}", "X"]
    }
  ]
}

bloom_level must be one of: remember | understand | apply | analyze | evaluate | create

Respond with valid JSON only. No markdown fences. No extra text.
